N. sativa belongs to family Ranunculaceae and it is possibly one of the most significant medicinal plants in history. It is mentioned in different historical and religious text books. In southern Asia, the seed of this plant is popularly known as ‘Kalonji’ in the middle east most common name is ‘habbat us sauda’ and popular name of this plant in English is ‘black cumin’ (
Gilani et al., 2004; 
Tavakkoli et al., 2017).
